  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 3. Twelve of thirteen factors are assessed and meet required levels. One factor (Use error) carries factorStatus 'not-assessed' on the grounds that operator interaction is considered irrelevant to an automated CFD pipeline; however, the correct encoding for an inapplicable factor would be 'not-applicable', and the absence of a formal assessment at MRL 3 materially weakens credibility.",
